ga]]<br /> VMI\n|4\u20131\n|William & Mary leaves the Southern Conference.<ref name=\"SoConMembers\"/>\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1978 NCAA Division I-A football season|1978]]\n|[[Furman Paladins football|Furman]]<br /> Chattanooga\n|4\u20131\n|Division I splits into [[NCAA Division I Football Bowl Subdivision|I-A]] and [[NCAA Division I#Football Championship Subdivision|I-AA]] subdivisions.<ref>On August 1, 1973 the NCAA's membership was divided into three legislative and competitive divisions at the first special convention ever held. All major schools were reclassified as [[NCAA Division I|Division I]] and other schools were divided into [[NCAA Division II|Division II]] and [[NCAA Division III|Division III]]. Roman numerals were chosen to be used rather than the Arabic 1, 2, 3. In 1978, Division I members voted to create subclassifications I-A, I-AA, and I-AAA for the sport of football. The major difference (at this point) besides sponsorship is the amount of scholarships allotted. I-A gets 85, I-AA gets 63, and I-AAA is for institutions that do not sponsor football. Only NCAA Division I is divided into subclassifications and only in the sport of football.</ref><br /> East Tennessee State joins the Southern Conference.<ref name=\"SoConMembers\"/>\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1979 NCAA Division I-A football season|1979]]\n|Chattanooga\n|5\u20131\n|\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1980 NCAA Division I-A football season|1980]]\n|Furman\n|7\u20130\n|\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1981 NCAA Division I-A football season|1981]]\n|Furman\n|5\u20132\n|\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1982 NCAA Division I-AA football season|1982]]\n|Furman\n|6\u20131\n|Southern Conference drops from I-A to the I-AA classification in football.<ref name=\"SoConH\"/>\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1983 NCAA Division I-AA football season|1983]]\n|Furman\n|6\u20130\u20131\n|\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1984 NCAA Division I-AA football season|1984]]\n|Chattanooga\n|5\u20131\n|\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1985 NCAA Division I-AA football season|1985]]\n|Furman\n|6\u20130\n|\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1986 NCAA Division I-AA football season|1986]]\n|[[Appalachian State Mountaineers football|Appalachian State]]\n|6\u20130\u20131\n|\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1987 NCAA Division I-AA football season|1987]]\n|Appalachian State\n|7\u20130\n|\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1988 NCAA Division I-AA football season|1988]]\n|[[1988 Furman Paladins football team|Furman]]<br />[[1988 Marshall Thundering Herd football team|Marshall]]\n|6\u20131\n|Furman wins NCAA Division I-AA [[NCAA Division I Football Championship|national championship]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Furman to honor 1988 national champs|author=Willie T. Smith III|publisher=The Greenville News|date=2008-11-14|accessdate=2008-12-16|url=http://www.greenvilleonline.com/article/20081114/SPORTS0103/811140319/1002}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref>\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1989 NCAA Division I-AA football season|1989]]\n|[[1989 Furman Paladins football team|Furman]]\n|7\u20130\n|\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1990 NCAA Division I-AA football season|1990]]\n|[[1990 Furman Paladins football team|Furman]]\n|6\u20131\n|\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1991 NCAA Division I-AA football season|1991]]\n|[[1991 Appalachian State Mountaineers football team|Appalachian State]]\n|6\u20131\n|Georgia Southern joins the Southern Conference.<ref name=\"SoConMembers\"/>\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1992 NCAA Division I-AA football season|1992]]\n|[[1992 The Citadel Bulldogs football team|The Citadel]]\n|6\u20131\n|[[1992 Marshall Thundering Herd football team|Marshall]] wins NCAA Division I-AA national championship.<ref name=\"IAATitles\">{{cite web|title=NCAA History: FCS History|publisher=NCAA|accessdate=2008-12-16|url=https://www.ncaa.com/history/football-fcs.html|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120918104729/http://www.ncaa.com/history/football-fcs.html|archivedate=2012-09-18}}</ref>\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1993 NCAA Division I-AA football season|1993]]\n|[[1993 Georgia Sou