irst special convention ever held. All major schools were reclassified as [[NCAA Division I|Division I]] and other schools were divided into [[NCAA Division II|Division II]] and [[NCAA Division III|Division III]]. Roman numerals were chosen to be used rather than the Arabic 1, 2, 3. In 1978, Division I members voted to create subclassifications I-A, I-AA, and I-AAA for the sport of football. The major difference (at this point) besides sponsorship is the amount of scholarships allotted. I-A gets 85, I-AA gets 63, and I-AAA is for institutions that do not sponsor football. Only NCAA Division I is divided into subclassifications and only in the sport of football.</ref><br /> East Tennessee State joins the Southern Conference.<ref name=\"SoConMembers\"/>\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1979 NCAA Division I-A football season|1979]]\n|Chattanooga\n|5\u20131\u20130\n|\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1980 NCAA Division I-A football season|1980]]\n|Furman\n|7\u20130\u20130\n|\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1981 NCAA Division I-A football season|1981]]\n|Furman\n|5\u20132\u20130\n|\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1982 NCAA Division I-AA football season|1982]]\n|Furman\n|6\u20131\u20130\n|Southern Conference drops from I-A to the I-AA classification in football.<ref name=\"SoConH\"/>\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1983 NCAA Division I-AA football season|1983]]\n|Furman\n|6\u20130\u20131\n|\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1984 NCAA Division I-AA football season|1984]]\n|Chattanooga\n|5\u20131\u20130\n|\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1985 NCAA Division I-AA football season|1985]]\n|Furman\n|6\u20130\u20130\n|\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1986 NCAA Division I-AA football season|1986]]\n|[[Appalachian State Mountaineers football|Appalachian State]]\n|6\u20130\u20131\n|\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1987 NCAA Division I-AA football season|1987]]\n|Appalachian State\n|7\u20130\u20130\n|\n|-align=\"center\"\n|[[1988 NCAA Division I-AA football season|1988]]\n|[[1988 Furman Paladins football team|Furman]]<br />[[1988 Marshall Thundering Herd foot